msgid "Axis Locking"
msgstr "Bloqueio de eixos"

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/axis_locking.rst:10
msgid "Axis locking."
msgstr "O bloqueio de eixos."

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/axis_locking.rst:12
msgid "This option limits the transformation to the specified axis."
msgstr "Esta opção limita as transformações para o eixo especificado."

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/axis_locking.rst:14
msgid ":doc:`Transformations (translation/scale/rotation) </editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/introduction>` in *Object Mode* and *Edit Mode*, as well as extrusion in *Edit Mode*) can be locked to a particular axis relative to the current :doc:`transform orientation </editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/orientations>`. By locking a transformation to a particular axis you are restricting transformations to a single dimension."
msgstr "As :doc:`transformações (translation/scale/rotation) </editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/introduction>` no *Modo de objeto* e *Modo de edição*, bem como a extrusão no *Modo de edição* podem ser bloqueadas para um eixo em particular, em relação as :doc:`orientações de transformação </editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/orientations>`. Através do bloqueio para um dos eixos em particular, você estará, de fato, restringindo as transformações para uma única dimensão."

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/axis_locking.rst:22
msgid "Usage"
msgstr "Utilização"

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/axis_locking.rst:24
msgid "A locked axis will display in a brighter color than an unlocked axis. For example in the image to the right, the Z axis is drawn in light blue as movement is constrained to this axis. This example, can be achieved in two ways:"
msgstr "Um eixo bloqueado (travado) será mostrado em uma cor mais clara do que um eixo não travado. Por exemplo, na imagem a direita, o eixo Z é desenhado em azul claro devido ao fato do movimento estar restrito a este eixo. Este exemplo, pode ser obtido de duas maneiras:"

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/axis_locking.rst:29
msgid "Hotkey"
msgstr "Atalho"

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/axis_locking.rst:31
msgid "The axis of movement can be changed at any time during transformation by typing :kbd:`X`, :kbd:`Y`, :kbd:`Z`."
msgstr "O eixo de movimentação pode ser alterado a qualquer momento durante as transformações usando o atalho para o eixo especificado, como :kbd:`X`, :kbd:`Y` ou :kbd:`Z`."

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/axis_locking.rst:35
msgid "Pointing"
msgstr "Apontamento"

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/axis_locking.rst:39
msgid "Axis-Constraint in action."
msgstr "A restrição de eixos em ação."

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/axis_locking.rst:41
msgid "Holding :kbd:`MMB` after starting a transformation lets you select an axis to constrain to. A visual option to constrain the translation will be available, showing the three axes in the 3D View space. A dotted white line is used as a pointer. The axis of choice to confirm the operation will depend on the highlighted axis about which the :kbd:`MMB` is released."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/axis_locking.rst:47
msgid "When you already moved the mouse in the desired direction, pressing :kbd:`MMB` will lock to the axis which was pointed at."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/axis_locking.rst:52
msgid "Axis Locking Types"
msgstr "Tipo de bloqueio de eixos."

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/axis_locking.rst:57
#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/axis_locking.rst:73
msgid "Reference"
msgstr "Referência"

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/axis_locking.rst
msgid "Mode:     Object and Edit Modes (translate, rotate, scale, extrude)"
msgstr "Modo:     Modo de objeto e Modo de edição (Mover, Rotacionar, Escalonar, Executar extrusão)"

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/axis_locking.rst
msgid "Hotkey:   :kbd:`X`, :kbd:`Y`, :kbd:`Z` or :kbd:`MMB` after moving the mouse in the desired direction."
msgstr "Atalho:   :kbd:`X`, :kbd:`Y`, :kbd:`Z` ou :kbd:`BMM` após mover o mouse na direção desejada."

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/axis_locking.rst:63
msgid "Axis locking limits the transformation to a single axis (or forbids transformations along two axes). An object, face, vertex or other selectable item will only be able to move, scale or rotate in a single dimension."
msgstr "O bloqueio limita as transformações para um único eixo (ou proíbe as transformações ao longo de dois eixos). Objetos, faces, vértices ou outros itens selecionáveis serão capazes de ser movidos, escalonados ou rotacionados em uma única dimensão."

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/axis_locking.rst:71
msgid "Plane Locking"
msgstr "Bloqueio em planos"

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/axis_locking.rst
msgid "Mode:     Object and Edit Modes (translate, scale)"
msgstr "Modo:     Modo de objeto e Modo de edição (Mover, Escalonar)"

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/axis_locking.rst
msgid "Hotkey:   :kbd:`Shift-X`, :kbd:`Shift-Y`, :kbd:`Shift-Z` or :kbd:`Shift-MMB` after moving the mouse in the desired direction."
msgstr "Atalho:   :kbd:`Shift-X`, :kbd:`Shift-Y`, :kbd:`Shift-Z` ou :kbd:`Shift-BMM` após mover o mouse na direção desejada."

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/axis_locking.rst:84
msgid "Plane locking."
msgstr "O bloqueio em planos."

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/axis_locking.rst:87
msgid "Plane locking locks the transformation to *two* axes (or forbids transformations along one axis), thus creating a plane in which the element can be moved or scaled freely. Plane locking only affects translation and scaling."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/axis_locking.rst:92
msgid "Note that for rotation, both axis and plane locking have the same effect because a rotation is always constrained around one axis. *Trackball* type rotations :kbd:`R-R` cannot be locked at all."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/axis_locking.rst:98
msgid "Axis Locking Modes"
msgstr "Modos de bloqueio de eixos"

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/axis_locking.rst:103
msgid "Axis locking modes."
msgstr "Os modos de bloqueio de eixos."

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/axis_locking.rst:105
msgid "A and B show Z axis locking in *Global* and *Normal* orientations respectively. C and D show the same situation with face selection, E and F with edge selection and G and H with vertex selection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/axis_locking.rst:109
msgid "A single key press constrains movement to the corresponding *Global* axis. A second key press of the *same* key constrains movement to the current transform orientation selection (except if it is set to *Global*, in which case the *Local* orientation is used). Finally, a third key press of the same key removes constraints."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/axis_locking.rst:115
msgid "The orientation can be set in the :doc:`Transform Orientation </editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/orientations>` selector of the 3D View header."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/axis_locking.rst:121
msgid "For example, if the current transform orientation is set to *Normal*, pressing :kbd:`G` to start translation, followed by :kbd:`Z` will lock translation in the Z direction relative to the *Global* orientation, pressing :kbd:`Z` again will lock translation to the Z axis relative to the *Normal* orientation. Pressing :kbd:`Z` again will remove all constraints. The current mode will be displayed in the left hand side of the *3D View header*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/axis_locking.rst:128
msgid "As can be seen in the *Axis locking modes* image, the direction of the transform also takes into account the selection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/axis_locking.rst:131
msgid "Note that using a locked axis does not prevent you from using the keyboard to enter :doc:`numeric transformation </editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/numeric_input>` values."
msgstr ""

